title: Bartram Trail's Joey Gatewood runs in two-point conversion in OT to beat Ponte Vedra 52-51
text:
Bartram Trail's Joey Gatewood runs in two-point conversion in OT to beat Ponte Vedra 52-51 
Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 12:27 am | updated Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 4:10 am 
BARTRAM TRAIL 52 
PONTE VEDRA (OT) 51 
Star of the game: QB Joey Gatewood had 248 rushing yards on 18 carries, threw for 67 yards and ran in a game-ending two-point conversion as the visiting Bears beat Ponte Vedra in overtime in a non-district shootout. 
Turning point: After Bartram Trail matched Ponte Vedra’s touchdown in overtime, Bears coach Darrell Sutherland opted to go for the two-point conversion and the win as Gatewood ran for the score. 
On defense: After Ponte Vedra tied the game 44-44 on a Nick Tronti touchdown pass to Marshall Few in the fourth quarter, Bartram Trail’s Jordan Helm tackled Ponte Vedra kicker Chris Howard on the conversion attempt to keep the game tied. 
Fast facts: Jarret Stepp had an 87-yard kickoff return for Ponte Vedra. ... Bartram Trail connected on a double-pass touchdown from Dallas Gieger to AJ Bolden. ... Tronti had a 50-yard rushing touchdown on a zone-read play. ... Tronti had 297 yards passing. ... Bartram Trail receiver Chandler Harvin had two touchdown receptions and 112 receiving yards. 
They said it: “I’m proud of the kids. The way they persevered in the face of adversity. That is what high school football should be like.” — Bartram Trail coach Darrell Sutherland 
Matt Potak For the Times-Union
